rmation for product costing for a webpage and fixed problems in several existing programs (Balance Sheet, Depreciation, Internal Orders, etc.).\r\nFrom Mar-2005 to Feb 2007    \r\nEffem Mexico / Masterfoods Mexico (SAP Enterprise and 4.0)\r\no	Since March/2006 I was part of the GSM team, giving support to all FI functional modules (FI, CO, PA, TR, AM, IM, etc.) for Mexico, Peru, Columbia, Venezuela, Puerto Rico, EU, Dominican Republic and CEIPA, as well as part-time support to all European and Asian sites, evaluating new requirements that might need a development and discussing them with the regional and global teams.\r\no	From March/2005 to February/2006 I was part of the rollout implementation team for Atlas project in Lucas, responsible for all financial interfaces and conversions, both, in the new system (LSMWs in SAP4.7) and the old system (SAP 4.0 ABAP developments), as well as fixed assets and investment management validation. This project consisted on implementing the company on top of an existing and totally productive company, sharing the same company code in a shared regional instance and was the first to be completed on time.\r\no	From March/2005 to February/2006 I was responsible for all ABAP developments (new requirements and support) in the previous SAP system (SAP 4.0) for Lucas, as well as supporting FI modules as functional and Basis Support (Security, printers and transports).\r\n\r\nJan-2005 – Mar-2005\r\nSigma Foods / SACHS Automotive (SAP 3.1F and 4.0)\r\n\r\no	During this time I worked in several ABAP requirements (FI, SD, MM) for these companies, including legal vendor/customer reports, Physical changes module, Service level reports, transportation module and deliveries enhancements.\r\n\r\nJun-2004 – Dec-2004   \r\nEffem Mexico (SAP 4.0)\r\no	During this time I developed interfaces between SAP and the FPPS system, and supported and fixed programs from SD, FI and MM. \r\no	Also worked as Master Data, covering Material, Vendor, BOM and Purchase Price management, along with Basis support.\r\n\r\nJan-2004 – Apr-2004   \r\nJanssen Cilag de Mexico (SAP Enterprise implementation)\r\no	I was part of the Implementation team for project Solar (led by IBM), covering Mexico, Brazil, Argentina and Venezuela, and responsible of designing and developing Material, Batch, Vendor and Customer Master Conversions, PO and Initial stock uploading, Batch determination enhancement, as well as a small coverage for Basis Support (role management and transport support) during stress tests and special consultancy to developers in SD, FI, CO and PP modules. \r\n\r\nJan-1996 – Dec-2003   \r\nBritish American Tobacco / Cigarrera La Moderna (SAP 4.5B Implementation/support))\r\n•	Role and Responsibilities:\r\no	From Oct/2003 to Dec/2003, I worked on the analysis of the RICE utilization and Data Cleaning project for FI, CO, MM, SD, PA, PP, RH, PM and Basis modules, as well as developing RFCs for the tracking project.\r\no	From Dec/2001 to Jun/2003 I worked as Basis administrator and  ABAP consultant. During this period I redesigned and implemented a license management procedure that saved the company more than USD250,000 on license fees. Apart from giving expert ABAP and Basis consultancy to many projects such as V3, Intelligia Payroll, travel expenses, MES, transportation, Akkade, Micro marketing, salary budget, etc. I was responsible for quality assurance and IT security, and as Regional IT security coordinator, responsible for performing BAT Central America IT audit held in Costa Rica.\r\no	From Feb/2000 to Dec/2001 I was leader of the development team implementing 2nd and 3rd wave of SAP in the company, comprising the following modules: PA, PC, PP, PM, RH and WF, dropping issues down to less than a half of those on the 1st wave. Also lead the ABAP team for the archiving project and because of optimization processes and helping in accomplishing the department goals, I was awarded with the IT Team player Award in 2000 and 2001.\r\no